==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
Originally {{zh-l|*𧷓}}, an {{Han compound|nocap=1|出|買|t1=[[go out]]|t2=[[buy]]|ls=ic|ls2=psc|c1=s|c2=p}}.

{{zh-l|*出}}, which indicates [[exoactive]] semantics ({{zh-ref|Sagart, 1999}}), was eventually reduced to the etymologically unrelated {{zh-l|*士}}.

Unrelated to {{zh-l|*𧶠}}, which is used as a phonetic component in a number of characters.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|s=卖|alt=売,𧷓,𧷵,𧷨}}
{{och-l|買|to [[buy]]}} + {{IPAfont|/-s/}} (exoactive) → {{och-l|賣|to [[cause]] to buy → to sell}}

[[exoactive|Exoactive]] of {{och-l|買|to buy}} ({{zh-ref|Sagart, 1995}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}), from {{der|zh|sit-pro|*laj}}; see there for more. 

